The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	East Bengal and Mohun Bagan will face-off for the first time in the season on August 5 at the Salt Lake Stadium, it was decided in a league sub-committee meeting on Saturday. The Mohammedan Sporting vs CPT match in the Calcutta Football League, which was earlier scheduled for Tuesday, will be held on Thursday.            
	THE FIXTURE (likely)      
	July 31: Md. Sp. vs CPT (Salt Lake Stadium); Aug 1: EB vs Peerless (Howrah Stadium); United SC vs Railway FC (Mohun Bagan); Aug 2: MB vs George Telegraph (Mohun Bagan); Aug 4: Md. Sp. vs United SC (venue not decided); Aug 5: EB vs MB (Salt Lake Stadium)                
	 Ghanaian defender Suley Musah, who played for Air India last season, reached the city on Saturday. The defender, according to an East Bengal official, will sign on Monday and is likely to play in Tuesdays match against United SC.                
	 The Sahara Calcutta Football League Premier Division match between Peerless SC and CPT ended in a goalless draw at the Mohun Bagan ground on Saturday.                
	 East Bengal beat Mohammedan Sporting 4-1 in the ONGC Bengal Premier League table tennis championship at the All-India Refinery Employees Club on Saturday.                 
	 Karachi Grammar beat M.P. Birla in senior boys scull category of the BRC International School Regatta at Rabindra Sarobar on Saturday.           
	Regatta: International schools meet at Bengal Rowing Club from 8 am.                                                                                                                                                                      
